206
00:10:50,000 --> 00:10:57,000
We can do that with... origami. It's the sushi of paper.

207
00:10:57,000 --> 00:11:02,000
This idea hasn't gripped me. What else did you come up with?

208
00:11:02,000 --> 00:11:06,000
Well, I had to memorize the presentation, Robert, and it took a long time to build the swan, so...

209
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:07,000
That was bad.

210
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:14,000
If your woman is like mine, I bet you come home to hear the same thing all the time.

211
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:20,000
This paper is so hard. It scratches. Why can't there be a paper just for me?

212
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:29,000
Well, now there is. Paper. Paper for women. It's pink, scented, and silky soft.

213
00:11:29,000 --> 00:11:33,000
Now you can watch the game, and she can write a letter to her sister.

